-- ===== RISK LANGUAGE (always-included compliance) =====
($KB$Do Not Say / Safe phrases (founder safety rules)$KB$, $KB$Compliance - Do Not Say (Founder)$KB$,
$KB$Never make fake promises and never guarantee: ROI, capital appreciation, rental yield, premium, allocation, discount, Golden Visa approval, resale before handover, developer delivery date, or future market direction. Agents must NOT say: Dubai always goes up; every property in Dubai makes money; this will definitely double; there is no risk; you cannot lose money in Dubai; prices will definitely increase from September; the bull run is guaranteed; this project will definitely sell on premium; Golden Visa is guaranteed; ROI is guaranteed; Emaar is guaranteed profit; Business Bay is always good because it is next to Downtown; Palm Jumeirah will still double from here; JVC is always good for investment; Palm Jebel Ali will definitely become the next Palm Jumeirah; Tilal Al Ghaf will keep doubling. Agents SHOULD say: Dubai moves in cycles; the right project can perform well; entry price is critical; developer quality matters; location and payment plan matter; not every property performs the same; we need to compare the project properly; this has potential, but we must evaluate the numbers; subject to availability and developer confirmation. Safe phrases: subject to availability; subject to developer confirmation; subject to authority approval; based on current market information; this is a founder market view, not a guarantee; we must verify the latest details before confirming; the entry price must be studied carefully. Protect Amber Homes credibility - never use founder knowledge to pressure a client dishonestly, never quote confidential internal strategy or allocation advantage to a client, and never say Saad guarantees.$KB$,
$KB$do not say, compliance, safe phrases, guarantee, roi, golden visa, premium, appreciation, never say, risk language, credibility$KB$,
'all','active',1,'Founder KB v2 (Market, Developer, Community)'),

($KB$Founder master instruction: think like an advisor, not a listing sender$KB$, $KB$Founder's Knowledge$KB$,
$KB$Founder master instruction: guide agents to think like investment advisors, not listing senders. Always evaluate developer, location, entry price, payment plan, product type, resale demand, rental demand, current market cycle, the client's objective and holding period. Core view: Dubai is one of the world's strongest markets, but it rewards intelligent buying, not blind buying. Emaar is the number one master developer and a strong long-term brand; Meraas, Nakheel, Dubai Holding, Emaar, Majid Al Futtaim, Omniyat, Beyond, H&H, Aldar and Modon can create strong opportunities when the entry price is right; evaluate private developers carefully. Mature communities are often better for end-use and rental stability than fast appreciation; early-stage waterfront, family communities, townhouses, villas and strong master-developer projects can offer better upside if bought correctly. Always ask the client's purpose first, give a reason for every recommendation, avoid guarantees, and move serious clients toward a call, meeting, site visit, shortlist, EOI or booking. Remind agents: you make money when you buy correctly, not only when you sell.$KB$,
$KB$master instruction, advisor, how to think, closing, purpose, eoi, booking, meeting, site visit, strategy, buy correctly$KB$,
'all','active',1,'Founder KB v2 (Market, Developer, Community)');

